.TH LOOTSHEET-LOOT-APPRAISE 1 "Mar 2026" "LootSheet" "LootSheet Manual"
.SH NAME
lootsheet-loot-appraise \\- Record an off-ledger appraisal
.SH SYNOPSIS
lootsheet loot appraise [flags]
.SH DESCRIPTION
LootSheet CLI

Usage:
  lootsheet loot appraise --id ID --value AMOUNT --date YYYY-MM-DD [--appraiser TEXT] [--notes TEXT]

Examples:
  lootsheet loot appraise --id loot-123 --value 75GP --date 2026-03-08 --appraiser "Guild jeweler"
  lootsheet loot appraise --id loot-123 --value 80GP --date 2026-03-09 --notes "Second opinion"
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
--appraiser=string
who appraised the item (default: )
.TP
--date=string
appraisal date in YYYY-MM-DD (required) (default: )
.TP
-h, --help
help for appraise
.TP
--id=string
loot item ID (required) (default: )
.TP
--notes=string
appraisal notes (default: )
.TP
--value=string
appraised value (required) (default: )
.SH SEE ALSO
lootsheet-loot(1)
